{"info": {"author": "Barry Barrette", "author_email": "barrybarrette@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": [], "description": "# py-emails\n[![Build Status](https://travis-ci.org/whitebarry/py-emails.svg?branch=master)](https://travis-ci.org/whitebarry/py-emails)\n[![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/repos/github/whitebarry/py-emails/badge.svg)](https://coveralls.io/github/whitebarry/py-emails)\n\n\nSimple wrapper around `email` and `smtplib` for composing and sending email messages in an intuitive, simple interface.\nPure python, no dependencies outside of the standard library\n\n\n## Installation and use\nInstall with pip or your favorite package manager: `pip install py-emails`\n\n\nEmails can be created declaratively:\n```python\nfrom emails import Email\n\nsmtp_config = {\n    'sender': 'you@example.com',\n    'host': 'smtp.example.com'\n}\n\nfirst_attachment = {\n    'filename': 'example.png', \n    'content': open('example.png', 'rb').read()\n}\nother_attachment = {\n    'filename': 'example.csv', \n    'content': open('example.csv', 'rb').read()\n}\nmy_email = Email( \n    smtp_config, \n    subject='How are you?',\n    body='Long time no see, we should get together!',\n    attachments=[first_attachment, other_attachment]\n)\n```\n\nOr using a template dictionary:\n```python\nfrom emails import from_template\n\nsmtp_config = {\n    'sender': 'you@example.com',\n    'host': 'smtp.example.com',\n    'port': 587,\n    'password': '<secret password>'\n}\ntemplate = {\n    'smtp_config': smtp_config,\n    'subject': 'How are you?',\n    'body': 'Long time no see, we should get together!'\n}\nmy_email = from_template(template)\n```\n\n\nOnce you have the email object, sending it is as simple as specifying one or more recipients:\n```python\nimport emails\n\nsmtp_config = {\n    'sender': 'you@example.com',\n    'host': 'smtp.example.com'\n}\nmy_email = emails.Email(smtp_config)\nmy_email.send('person1@example.com')\nmy_email.send(['person2@example.com', 'person3@example.com'])\n```\n\nSee `examples.py` for more in depth use cases\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/whitebarry/py-emails", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "py-emails", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/py-emails/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/py-emails/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/whitebarry/py-emails"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/py-emails/1.1.0/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "Simple wrapper around email and smtplib for composing and sending email messages in an intuitive, simple interface.", "version": "1.1.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>py-emails</h1>\n<p><a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/whitebarry/py-emails\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Build Status\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/d1c6806d192662886652ff005cc4f477b1a12614/68747470733a2f2f7472617669732d63692e6f72672f776869746562617272792f70792d656d61696c732e7376673f6272616e63683d6d6173746572\"></a>\n<a href=\"https://coveralls.io/github/whitebarry/py-emails\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img alt=\"Coverage Status\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/f9857dc0f48b049ed0e32a4f59376efc2ef7f316/68747470733a2f2f636f766572616c6c732e696f2f7265706f732f6769746875622f776869746562617272792f70792d656d61696c732f62616467652e737667\"></a></p>\n<p>Simple wrapper around <code>email</code> and <code>smtplib</code> for composing and sending email messages in an intuitive, simple interface.\nPure python, no dependencies outside of the standard library</p>\n<h2>Installation and use</h2>\n<p>Install with pip or your favorite package manager: <code>pip install py-emails</code></p>\n<p>Emails can be created declaratively:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">emails</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">Email</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">smtp_config</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"s1\">'sender'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s1\">'you@example.com'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"s1\">'host'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s1\">'smtp.example.com'</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">first_attachment</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"s1\">'filename'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s1\">'example.png'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> \n    <span class=\"s1\">'content'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nb\">open</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'example.png'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'rb'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">read</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"n\">other_attachment</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"s1\">'filename'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s1\">'example.csv'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> \n    <span class=\"s1\">'content'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"nb\">open</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'example.csv'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'rb'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">read</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"n\">my_email</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Email</span><span class=\"p\">(</span> \n    <span class=\"n\">smtp_config</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> \n    <span class=\"n\">subject</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s1\">'How are you?'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">body</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s1\">'Long time no see, we should get together!'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">attachments</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">first_attachment</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">other_attachment</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<p>Or using a template dictionary:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">emails</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">from_template</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">smtp_config</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"s1\">'sender'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s1\">'you@example.com'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"s1\">'host'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s1\">'smtp.example.com'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"s1\">'port'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"mi\">587</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"s1\">'password'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s1\">'&lt;secret password&gt;'</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"n\">template</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"s1\">'smtp_config'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">smtp_config</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"s1\">'subject'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s1\">'How are you?'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"s1\">'body'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s1\">'Long time no see, we should get together!'</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"n\">my_email</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">from_template</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">template</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<p>Once you have the email object, sending it is as simple as specifying one or more recipients:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">emails</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">smtp_config</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"p\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"s1\">'sender'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s1\">'you@example.com'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"s1\">'host'</span><span class=\"p\">:</span> <span class=\"s1\">'smtp.example.com'</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"n\">my_email</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">emails</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Email</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">smtp_config</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">my_email</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">send</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'person1@example.com'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">my_email</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">send</span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"s1\">'person2@example.com'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'person3@example.com'</span><span class=\"p\">])</span>\n</pre>\n<p>See <code>examples.py</code> for more in depth use cases</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7034439, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "b79e2b53cd6e0ab96dd86e84bf5bd992", "sha256": "662c8cdb61dc4cc8fe24febc65ae9f55239bdc0c1bad4d45fcf76148468b4892"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "py_emails-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "b79e2b53cd6e0ab96dd86e84bf5bd992", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 3339, "upload_time": "2020-02-27T04:30:11", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-02-27T04:30:11.135133Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/e4/15/d5363a6c9cfeab526fedd7a2bdd60a16f0f18e7704bfe45f650ffc697bd7/py_emails-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests":